LAFIA â€“ A group under the aegis of Volunteers Youth Frontier for Governor of Nasarawa State on Monday urged immediate past senator representing Southern part of Nasarawa State, Senator Sulieman Adokwe to join the State governorship race come 2023. The group in a press statement signed by their spoke person Comrade Elisha Ebuga Yohanna, and made to newsmen in Lafia the state capital. Comr. Elisha Yohanna, said some PDP loyalist had acknowledege the contributions of Adokwe while in National Assembly; adding that he is the most suitable person for the job come 2023. Yohanna, mentioned some qualities of senator Sulieman Adokwe, to include party loyalty, humbleness, steadfastness and respect for the party. He said the fact available before the group was Adokwe has improved the living condition of the people of Nasarawa South Senatorial District through direct investment in critical sectors of education, economic, health and youths empowerment. Yohanna further mentioned some of his achievement to include: Education sector in Nasarawa State, empower the younger generation, construction and renovation of class room in 30 villages in Nasarawa State among others.